Package wt.vc.sessioniteration Description

vc.sessioniteration package � Session Iteration Service

The session iteration service provides a light-weight work-in-progress mechanism similar to the work in progress (WIP) service (wt.vc.wip package).�

 

The concepts known as checkout, checkin and undo-checkout in the WIP service are analogous respectively to the concepts of create, commit and delete in the session iteration service.

 

Analogous rules apply to SessionEditedIterations as to Workables.� Just as you must �checkout� a Workable to modify it you must �create a session iteration� of a SessionEditedIteration to modify it.� Once you have committed the session iteration it becomes un-modifiable similar to checkin.

 

The service also emits PRE and POST events for each of these basic actions: �create�, �commit� and �delete�.��
